{"type":"message","id":"eb6a4f54","parentId":"6981df40","timestamp":"2026-04-03T12:15:27.870Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_OQVPoGMX8RvAvj8Gf4sePZvs","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Search: site:bls.gov OR site:federalreserve.gov OR site:bea.gov CPI PPI nonfarm payroll unemployment rate PCE FOMC Powell April 2026\n**Engine**: tavily\n\n### Answer\n\nThe Producer Price Index (PPI) for April 2026 release is scheduled for May 13, 2026. Federal Reserve Chair Powell's speech on economic outlook was published in August 2025. The Federal Open Market Committee (FOMC) aims for maximum employment and price stability.\n\n---\n\n### Results (8)\n\n- **Schedule of Releases for the Producer Price Index** (41%)\n  https://www.bls.gov/schedule/news_release/ppi.htm\n  | * BY MONTH  * FEBRUARY 2026 * MARCH 2026 * APRIL 2026 * MAY 2026 * JUNE 2026 * JULY 2026 * AUGUST 2026 * SEPTEMBER 2026 * OCTOBER 2026 * NOVEMBER 2026 * DECEMBER 2026 * ENTIRE YEAR, 2026 * PRIOR YEARS  * BY NEWS RELEASE * BUSINESS EMPLOYMENT DYNAMICS * CONSUMER PRICE INDEX * COUNTY EMPLOYMENT AND WAGES * EMPLOYER COSTS FOR EMPLOYEE COMPENSATION * EMPLOYMENT COST INDEX * EMPLOYMENT SITUATION * JO...\n\n- **[PDF] Speech by Chair Powell on the economic outlook and framework ...** (22%)\n  https://www.federalreserve.gov/newsevents/speech/files/powell20250822.pdf\n  Johannsen, and David López-Salido (2025), “The Origins, Structure, and Results of the Federal Reserve’s 2019–20 Review of Its Monetary Policy Framework,” Finance and Economics Discussion Series 2025-065 (Washington: Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System, August), https://doi.org/10.17016/FEDS.2025.065 . Martin (2025), “Implications of Inflation Dynamics for Monetary Policy Strategy,” Fi...\n\n- **[PDF] Monetary Policy Report, February 2025 - Federal Reserve** (17%)\n  https://www.federalreserve.gov/publications/files/20250207_mprfullreport.pdf\n  vii Abbreviations AFE advanced foreign economy AI artificial